"use strict";(globalThis.webpackChunkkubestellar_docs_initiative=globalThis.webpackChunkkubestellar_docs_initiative||[]).push([[8130],{7735(e){e.exports=JSON.parse('{"archive":{"blogPosts":[{"id":"mentorship-opportunity","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/mentorship-opportunity","editUrl":"https://github.com/kubestellar/kubestellar/edit/main/kdemo/blog/2026-02-11-mentorship-opportunity.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-02-11-mentorship-opportunity.md","title":"Mentorship Opportunity: Build the Future of KubeStellar Onboarding","description":"Opportunity Summary","date":"2026-02-11T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"lfx","permalink":"/blog/tags/lfx"},{"inline":true,"label":"mentorship","permalink":"/blog/tags/mentorship"},{"inline":true,"label":"kubernetes","permalink":"/blog/tags/kubernetes"},{"inline":true,"label":"docs","permalink":"/blog/tags/docs"}],"readingTime":1,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"KubeStellar Community","title":"CNCF Sandbox \u2014 Multi-cluster configuration management","url":"https://github.com/kubestellar/kubestellar","imageURL":"/img/logo.svg","key":"kubestellar","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"mentorship-opportunity","title":"Mentorship Opportunity: Build the Future of KubeStellar Onboarding","authors":["kubestellar"],"tags":["lfx","mentorship","kubernetes","docs"]},"unlisted":false,"nextItem":{"title":"Project Vision: From Zero to Multi-Cluster in 30 Minutes","permalink":"/blog/project-vision"}},"content":"## Opportunity Summary\\r\\n\\r\\nThis LFX Mentorship project focuses on **KubeStellar Documentation and Self-Service Enablement**\u2014creating a frictionless path for new users to adopt KubeStellar.\\r\\n\\r\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\r\\n\\r\\n## Timeline\\r\\n\\r\\n**LFX Mentorship 2026 Term 1** (March\u2013May) \u2014 **12 weeks**\\r\\n\\r\\n- **Weeks 1\u20132**: Audit deployments and document friction points  \\r\\n- **Weeks 3\u20134**: Draft Quickstart + run first user tests  \\r\\n- **Weeks 5\u20136**: Build and publish interactive Killercoda tutorial  \\r\\n- **Weeks 7\u20138**: Produce and publish a 5\u20137 module video series  \\r\\n- **Weeks 9\u201310**: Create a 20-issue troubleshooting guide  \\r\\n- **Weeks 11\u201312**: Deliver use-case docs + migration guides  \\r\\n\\r\\n## What You\u2019ll Build\\r\\n\\r\\nDeliverables include:\\r\\n\\r\\n- A **\u2264 30-minute Quickstart**\\r\\n- A **hands-on interactive tutorial** (Killercoda)\\r\\n- A **video series** (beginner \u2192 advanced)\\r\\n- A **troubleshooting guide** with error signatures and fixes\\r\\n- **Use-case patterns** and **migration playbooks**\\r\\n\\r\\n## Who Should Apply\\r\\n\\r\\nThis is a strong fit if you enjoy:\\r\\n\\r\\n- Turning complex systems into clear learning journeys\\r\\n- Writing docs that reduce support load and improve adoption\\r\\n- Building tutorials and validation scripts\\r\\n- Working in open source communities\\r\\n\\r\\n## How to Apply\\r\\n\\r\\nApplications are managed through the LFX Mentorship portal:\\r\\n\\r\\n`https://mentorship.lfx.linuxfoundation.org/`\\r\\n\\r\\n## Get Involved\\r\\n\\r\\n- Join the KubeStellar community on CNCF Slack (`#kubestellar-dev`)\\r\\n- Browse issues and discussions on GitHub\\r\\n- Try the prototype site and open feedback issues"},{"id":"project-vision","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/project-vision","editUrl":"https://github.com/kubestellar/kubestellar/edit/main/kdemo/blog/2026-02-10-project-vision.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-02-10-project-vision.md","title":"Project Vision: From Zero to Multi-Cluster in 30 Minutes","description":"The Problem","date":"2026-02-10T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"lfx","permalink":"/blog/tags/lfx"},{"inline":true,"label":"documentation","permalink":"/blog/tags/documentation"},{"inline":true,"label":"onboarding","permalink":"/blog/tags/onboarding"},{"inline":true,"label":"kubestellar","permalink":"/blog/tags/kubestellar"}],"readingTime":1.13,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"KubeStellar Community","title":"CNCF Sandbox \u2014 Multi-cluster configuration management","url":"https://github.com/kubestellar/kubestellar","imageURL":"/img/logo.svg","key":"kubestellar","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"project-vision","title":"Project Vision: From Zero to Multi-Cluster in 30 Minutes","authors":["kubestellar"],"tags":["lfx","documentation","onboarding","kubestellar"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Mentorship Opportunity: Build the Future of KubeStellar Onboarding","permalink":"/blog/mentorship-opportunity"}},"content":"## The Problem\\r\\n\\r\\nMulti-cluster Kubernetes is powerful\u2014but onboarding often isn\u2019t.\\r\\n\\r\\nNew users frequently hit friction early:\\r\\n- Toolchain mismatches (kubectl/helm/clusteradm/kflex versions)\\r\\n- Context confusion (hosting vs WDS vs ITS vs WECs)\\r\\n- \u201cIt installed, but nothing syncs\u201d (labels/selectors don\u2019t match)\\r\\n- Troubleshooting scattered across sources\\r\\n\\r\\nThe result: **time-to-first-success** balloons from minutes to hours.\\r\\n\\r\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\r\\n\\r\\n## The Vision\\r\\n\\r\\nDeliver a documentation and self-service experience that feels like:\\r\\n\\r\\n- **One clear path** to success (\u2264 30 minutes)\\r\\n- **Hands-on learning** without local setup (Killercoda tutorial)\\r\\n- **Fast diagnosis** when things go wrong (20 common issues + error signatures)\\r\\n- **Practical patterns** users can adopt immediately (use cases + migration guides)\\r\\n\\r\\n## Why KubeStellar\\r\\n\\r\\nKubeStellar simplifies multi-cluster operations with:\\r\\n\\r\\n- **WDS**: define workloads and policies once using native Kubernetes objects  \\r\\n- **ITS**: inventory + transport (OCM) to clusters  \\r\\n- **WECs**: run workloads and report status  \\r\\n- **BindingPolicy**: declare what goes where using labels  \\r\\n\\r\\nThis makes multi-cluster feel like single-cluster operations\u2014without rewriting your manifests.\\r\\n\\r\\n## What Success Looks Like\\r\\n\\r\\nWe measure success with outcomes that matter:\\r\\n\\r\\n- **\u2264 30 minutes** to first successful multi-cluster deployment\\r\\n- **\u2265 4/5** user satisfaction in external testing\\r\\n- **8+** new GitHub issues from new users (signal of engagement)\\r\\n- **2+** documentation PRs from users (signal of contribution readiness)\\r\\n\\r\\n## Next Steps\\r\\n\\r\\n- Explore the **[Quickstart Guide](/docs/quickstart)**  \\r\\n- See the **[Interactive Tutorial Preview](/docs/tutorials/interactive-tutorial-preview)**  \\r\\n- Use **[Troubleshooting](/docs/troubleshooting)** when blocked"}]}}')}}]);